These fourteen (14) individual elements of this prevention program work together to prevent accidental chemical releases.  The Champaign Terminal and its employees are committed to the standards required by these management programs. In addition to the above elements, MPLX also has specific prevention measures that are employed as part of the Terminal's operating procedures and engineering and administrative controls to help prevent,  identify, contain/control, and reduce the consequences of a release. These are summarized as follows:

General Risk Reduction and Safety Measures including:

-Engineering and construction in accordance with recognized industry and company standards;
-Equipment properly designed with protection from overpressure (pressure safety relief valves, etc.);
-Updated technical drawings, Piping & Instrument Diagrams and Process/Block Flow Diagrams;
-Operating systems monitored and controlled by trained Operators;
-Redundant control systems;
-Manual shutdown devices for critical systems;
-Scheduled inspection and testing of safety devices;
-Limited/secured facility access;
-Regular safety meetings and safety awareness programs;
-Routinely scheduled safety inspections and audits; and
-Frequent unit surveillance by operators.

General Release Mitigation including:

-Process and remotely operated shut-offs to limit release quantity (also actuated via a fusible element);
-Offload station check valve to minimize pull-away impacts;
-Strategically located valves to isolate leaks; and
-Smart-Hose with design break-away and self-closing valves on each end (also pull-away protection.)

General Emergency Response including:

-Emergency alert system;
-Periodic emergency training for employees;
-Communication systems with local emergency responders and regulatory agencies; and
